Interface FSObject

All Known Subinterfaces:
FSDirectory, FSEntry, FSFile
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractDirectory, FatBasicDirEntry, FatDirectory, FatDirEntry, FatFile, FatLfnDirectory, FatLfnDirEntry, FatObject, FatRootEntry, LfnEntry
public interface FSObject

This interface is the base interface for objects that are part of a FileSystem.

Author:
Ewout Prangsma < epr at jnode.org>

Method Detail

isValid

boolean isValid()
Is this object still valid. An object is not valid anymore if it has been removed from the filesystem. All invocations on methods (exception this method) of invalid objects must throw an IOException.

Gets the filesystem to which this object belongs.
